<P>
BRIEFLY: JOURNALISM: USC NAMES NEW DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Associated Press and CBS News foreign correspondent Murray Fromson has 
been named the new director of the University of Southern California's School 
of Journalism. 
</P>
<P>
 Fromson, who had been serving as interim director since July 1, was officially 
named director on Nov. 15 at an alumni banquet.  
</P>
<P>
 A West Los Angeles resident, Fromson, 65, covered historic events such as the 
Vietnam War and Martin Luther King's march to Selma and served as CBS 
correspondent in Moscow, covering three summit meetings. 
</P>
<P>
 "I am confident that Professor Fromson will provide the necessary leadership 
and vision to ensure the School of Journalism's success in the years to come," 
said Gerald Davison, interim dean of USC's Annenberg School for Communication. 
</P>
