<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES / BENJAMIN EPSTEIN: FOOD DRIVES FEED NEED TO HELP OTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BENJAMIN EPSTEIN, Benjamin Epstein is a free-lance writer who regularly 
contributes to the Times Orange County. Information for this column can be 
faxed to (714) 966-7790. Or phone (714) 966-7700. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Whether it's toys for toppings or toys for tamales -- or even cans for crema 
al caramello -- Christmas season charity drives are underway at a number of 
area restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
 Amici Trattoria makes sure you get your just desserts when you donate even one 
canned good, which will entitle you to the complimentary dessert of your 
choice. ( Crema al caramello is vanilla flan.) Packaged produce and unwrapped 
children's toys are also welcome. The drive continues through Dec. 23 and 
benefits FISH, a group dedicated to preventing homelessness in Irvine, Costa 
Mesa and Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Speaking of which, anchovies are but one choice of topping that the donation 
of a new, unwrapped toy can get you at BJ's Chicago Pizzerias, where more than 
a dozen topping possibilities range from homemade meatballs to fresh garlic. 
Toys will be picked up Dec. 16 as part of the Toys for Tots program. 
</P>
<P>
 At El Torito Grills, a new, unwrapped toy means $10 off any check of $25 or 
more. That drive runs through Dec. 20, and certificates are valid through Jan. 
15. Toys go to Share Our Selves (S.O.S.) of Costa Mesa, which provides 
emergency food, funds and shelter for those in immediate need.  
</P>
<P>
 Take a couple of toys: Start at the Costa Mesa El Torito Grill, then have 
dessert at Amici next door. 
</P>
<P>
 Amici Trattoria, 655 Anton Blvd., Costa Mesa, (714) 850-9399. 
</P>
<P>
 BJ's Chicago Pizzeria, 2430 S. Bristol St., Santa Ana (714) 557-5950. 
</P>
<P>
 BJ's Chicago Pizzeria, 106 Main St., Balboa, (714) 675-7560. 
</P>
<P>
 BJ's Chicago Pizzeria, 280 S. Coast Highway, Laguna Beach, (714) 494-3802. 
</P>
<P>
 BJ's Chicago Pizzeria, 31781 Camino Capistrano, San Juan Capistrano, (714) 
489-9771. 
</P>
<P>
 BJ's Chicago Pizzeria, 209 Main St., Seal Beach, (310) 594-9310. 
</P>
<P>
 BJ's Chicago Pizzeria, 200 Main St., Huntington Beach, (714) 374-2224. 
</P>
<P>
 El Torito Grill, 633 Anton Blvd., Costa Mesa, (714) 622-2672. 
</P>
<P>
 El Torito Grill, 1910 Main St., Irvine, (714) 975-1220. 
</P>
<P>
 El Torito Grill, 951 Newport Center Drive, Newport Beach, (714) 640-2875. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 'Tis the season to be bubbly, and Monday, Pascal salutes Perrier Jouet 
Champagne, known for the pretty Belle Epoque-style bottle with enamel flowers. 
A four-course dinner and as many cuvees of Jouet will feature roasted duck 
breast with saffron and cranberry couscous. The event begins at 6:30 p.m.; $80 
includes Christmas caroling but not tax or gratuity; The same meal sans 
champagne will be served throughout December for $49.50. 
</P>
<P>
 The staff at Sfuzzi was pleasantly surprised recently by the overwhelming 
response to the penultimate event of this year's Veni Vidi Vici Vino wine 
dinner series. Previous events had attracted an average of 50 tasters; 130 
turned out for Northern California-based Silver Oak Cellars, and a second night 
was offered.  
</P>
<P>
 On Monday at 7 p.m., Jordan Winery brings the series to a close with a 
four-course meal, including fire-grilled quail and rosemary-roasted lamb 
saddle. Wines to be served include a Chardonnay, two Cabernet sauvignons and 
"J" sparkling wine. It's $45 per person, not including tax or tip. 
</P>
<P>
 Pascal, 1000 N. Bristol St., Newport Beach (714) 752-0107. 
</P>
<P>
 Sfuzzi, 1870A Harbor Blvd., Suite 200, Costa Mesa (714) 548-9500. 
</P>
