<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; FREE PARK PASS FOR TOY DONORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK SABBATINI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Magic Mountain is offering free admission the next two weekends to anyone who 
donates a new toy worth $10 or more to the Toys for Tots drive, park officials 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The toys will be collected at the admissions gate by Marine Corps reserves, 
who will then distribute them to needy children throughout the Southland, said 
Palmer Moody, a spokesman for the amusement park. He said all toys should be 
new and not wrapped in Christmas paper. 
</P>
<P>
 Regular park admission for adults is $29, he added. 
</P>
<P>
 Magic Mountain has collected more than 250,000 toys in the decade that it has 
participated in the 47-year-old program, Moody said. MARK SABBATINI 
</P>
</TEXT>
