<TEXT>
<P>
 Dole Now Owns About 99.5% of Castle & Cooke: The Westlake Village-based food 
company said its Dole Acquisition Corp. unit accepted all 5,019,947 tendered 
shares in the Hawaiian real estate developer at $15.75 apiece and that it 
expects the merger to take place within 30 days. Under Hawaii law, Dole Food 
Co. said, it can complete the merger with Castle & Cooke Homes Inc. without the 
need for a vote of that company's shareholders. 
