<P>
AROUND THE VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 EL MONTE: The City Council has authorized the purchase of a police helicopter 
after renting one since September, 1993. The helicopter will cost $90,000 plus 
$400,000 for maintenance over the first five years and will allow more time in 
the air than the rented helicopter did. 
</P>
<P>
 GLENDORA: The council approved development plans for a Super K mart at Lone 
Hill Avenue and Gladstone Street, including 303,500 square feet of commercial 
space with the sale of alcoholic beverages, a satellite transmission facility 
and an automotive repair garage. 
</P>
<P>
 PASADENA: Council members placed a measure on the March ballot to limit the 
amount the city can take annually from its water and power company to 8% of its 
profits. The city currently takes about 10% of utility profits a year. 
</P>
<P>
 SOUTH PASADENA: Former Mayor Lee D. Prentiss will accept $500,000 from the 
city for violating his civil rights, his attorney said. A jury had awarded 
Prentiss $1.2 million after agreeing with his claim that city officials had 
withdrawn a building permit as political retaliation. A judge reduced the 
verdict last month. The City Council must agree to the settlement as well. 
</P>
