<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE BLOTTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA O'NEILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DIAMOND BAR: A 27-year-old Montclair man was killed Monday night in a 
hit-and-run accident on the Pomona (60) Freeway. Crispin Vazquez was hit at 
6:45 p.m. as he pulled over to the shoulder to investigate mechanical problems 
with his truck, authorities said. Vazquez was under the rear portion of the 
attached trailer when he was struck in the head by a car that did not stop. 
Anyone who witnessed the accident is asked to call (213) 669-4472 or (310) 
868-0503. 
</P>
<P>
 EL MONTE: A 58-year-old El Monte man died Saturday in a hit-and-run accident 
while he was walking across Valley Boulevard. Antonio Balderas suffered head 
and internal injuries and died at Greater El Monte Community Hospital five 
hours after the 7 p.m. accident. 
</P>
<P>
 EL MONTE: An 85-year-old woman was beaten to death Tuesday and her middle-aged 
daughter was assaulted, sheriff's deputies said. The incident occurred at about 
1:20 p.m in the 10000 block of Giovane Street. No further information was 
available. 
</P>
<P>
 MONROVIA: Police shot and wounded a 42-year-old man Saturday after he 
threatened police officers who responded to a call at his house. Douglas 
Rowland was shot in the upper torso and was in stable condition at Arcadia 
Methodist Hospital, police said. Police responded to a domestic dispute call at 
a home in the 200 block of N. Encinitas Avenue at about 6:30 p.m. When officers 
contacted Rowland, who lived at the house, he told them he was armed and that 
he would shoot any officer who came into his house. After a two-hour standoff, 
Rowland walked out of the back door armed with a rifle and confronted officers. 
The officers ordered Rowland to drop his rifle and when he didn't comply, shot 
him. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: A 4-year-old Hollywood boy died Thursday after a 125-pound barbell 
fell on his chest. Jakeita Clayton died at Children's Hospital in Los Angeles 
at about 2:45 p.m. Jakeita was visiting relatives at a home in the 1300 block 
of Clovis Court and was playing alone in the back yard when he somehow managed 
to cause the barbell to fall from a weight bench, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: A 4-year-old Pomona boy was injured Thursday when he apparently ran 
into the path of a car. Jesus Orosco was taken to Pomona Valley Community 
Hospital for treatment of moderate injuries after the 1:15 p.m. accident, 
police said. Jesus was playing in an alleyway on Friar Lane when he ran into 
the path of a car driven by Gabriel Zamora, 22, of Pomona. Zamora was not 
cited. 
</P>
<P>
 WALNUT: A 33-year-old man committed suicide at 8 a.m. Tuesday by jumping from 
a building on the Mt. San Antonio College campus. The man, whose identity was 
not released because his relatives have not yet been notified, was taken to San 
Dimas Community Hospital, where he died a short time later, sheriff's deputies 
said. LISA O'NEILL 
</P>
