<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: ASTHMATIC TEACHER FILES ENDANGERMENT CLAIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A high school teacher claims the school's principal intentionally endangered 
his life by not allowing the teacher to seek medical care for his asthmatic 
condition. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruben Romero, a graphic arts and silk-screening instructor at Mark Keppel High 
School, said Principal Rudy Chavez has harassed him for complaining about a 
Feb. 3 incident in which Romero was not allowed to leave the school after 
suffering an asthma attack. 
</P>
<P>
 Romero's claim, filed with the school district Nov. 21, names Chavez and Heber 
Meeks, superintendent of the Alhambra City and High School Districts. Meeks and 
Chavez declined to comment. 
</P>
<P>
 Romero, who has taught at Mark Keppel for 24 years, said in the claim that he 
must use a special breathing machine when his asthma flares up. 
</P>
