<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; EDELMAN 
SUGGESTS DEPUTY FOR TEMPORARY COUNCIL SEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Departing Supervisor Ed Edelman said no thanks Wednesday to a suggestion that 
he temporarily fill Supervisor-elect Zev Yaroslavsky's City Council seat, but 
offered his chief deputy for the job instead.  
</P>
<P>
 Edelman held the council seat before Yaroslavsky and now will be succeeded by 
the Westside veteran on the County Board of Supervisors. 
</P>
<P>
 The supervisor strongly recommended "that the City Council give consideration 
to appointing my chief deputy, Bob Geoghegan, to the City Council's seat until 
July, 1995, when the new city councilman will be elected."  
</P>
<P>
 On Friday, Edelman -- who opted not to run for a sixth term -- will leave the 
Board of Supervisors after 20 years. Three days later, Yaroslavsky will be 
sworn in.  
</P>
<P>
 Fifth District residents are clamoring for an interim council replacement 
because they are worried that otherwise their interests will be ignored until 
July. Some people suggested that Edelman would be the perfect substitute until 
the new council member is elected. Yaroslavsky's wife, Barbara, is running for 
the seat. 
</P>
<P>
 The council can appoint a successor to Yaroslavsky with a simple majority vote 
but in the past has shied away from filling such vacancies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
