METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; SLAIN 
OFFICER'S WIDOW WILL KEEP HORSE HE RODE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beth Heim, the widow of the Los Angeles police officer gunned down last month 
in Hollywood, will get to keep the horse her husband rode as a member of the 
mounted unit of the LAPD's elite Metro Division. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council on Tuesday agreed that Heim should be sold 
Panzer, a part thoroughbred, part draft horse, for $1. 
</P>
<P>
 Officer Charles Heim had planned to buy the horse when he retired from the 
police force because he was worried that nobody else would be able to handle 
the cantankerous animal. 
</P>
<P>
 The council agreed to sell the animal to Beth Heim, also a police officer, for 
the nominal price, saying that the sale was for "a humanitarian purpose." 
</P>
