<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: VOLUNTEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Helping hands 
</P>
<P>
 SAN CLEMENTE 
</P>
<P>
 2 Students Assist at Doheny Center 
</P>
<P>
 Who: Katie Gililland and Lisette Polny 
</P>
<P>
 Contribution: The two San Clemente High School students volunteered 95 hours 
this past summer at the Doheny State Beach Interpretive Center. The center 
displays more than 100 marine animal species in several aquariums. In the 
summer, the center depends on a volunteer staff, mostly students, to remain 
open to the public. Gililland and Polny served as guides and cashiers, and did 
cleanup work at the center. Both students received a letter of thanks from the 
center. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 * FOUNTAIN VALLEY AND HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
<P>
 2 Groups Get Funds for Needy Youths 
</P>
<P>
 Who: Two programs providing sports opportunities for low-income youngsters 
</P>
<P>
 Contribution: The Girls and Boys Club of Fountain Valley-Huntington Beach and 
Students Run LA are among 11 Southland groups that will share in a $382,048 
grant from the Amateur Athletic Foundation of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 The Girls and Boys Club, also known as Kid Connection, was awarded an $8,800 
grant, which will be spent to resurface and restripe the club's play area. 
</P>
<P>
 Students Run LA, a running program serving at-risk youngsters in Orange, Los 
Angeles and San Diego counties, was awarded $50,400, which will be used to 
teach the value of goal setting and teamwork through long-distance running. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 * HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
<P>
 Libraries Receive Donated Furnishings 
</P>
<P>
 Who: Rockwell International Corp. in Anaheim and the Coast Community College 
District in Costa Mesa 
</P>
<P>
 Contribution: Donated furniture for the Huntington Beach Central Library and 
Oak View Branch Library. Rockwell donated 50 metal shelving units to be used in 
the central library's genealogy section. 
</P>
<P>
 The company also gave 70 wooden shelving units, a desk, file cabinet and table 
for the Oak View branch, scheduled to open in the spring. The college district 
donated five tables, a desk and a file cabinet, also to be used at the Oak View 
branch. 
</P>
<P>
 Items still needed for Oak View include stackable study chairs, computer 
equipment, adult study chairs and children's furnishings. For donation 
information, call (714) 960-8837.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
