<TEXT>
<P>
 An Oxnard man was seriously wounded Wednesday night in an apparent 
gang-related drive-by shooting in Oxnard's La Colonia neighborhood, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, who was not immediately identified, was walking alone on Colonia Road 
about 7 p.m. when he was shot in the shoulder from a passing car, Oxnard police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 He was in surgery at St. John's Regional Medical Center late Wednesday, but 
hospital officials would not characterize his condition. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is pretty well confirmed it was a gang shooting," Police Cmdr. Bob Elder 
said. 
</P>
