<P>
WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL; LOYOLA MARYMOUNT ELIMINATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arizona defeated Loyola Marymount, 15-13, 9-15, 15-6, 15-13, in the first 
round of the NCAA tournament in Tucson, Ariz., on Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lions led by at least three points in each game, but could not hold off 
the Wildcats. 
</P>
<P>
 In the fourth game, the Lions (19-10) jumped to a 4-0 lead, but the Wildcats 
won the next five points, extended their lead to 9-6, and later won the final 
six points to close out the match. 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter Kim Blankenship had 12 kills for the Lions. Mardell Wrensch 
added 11. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are a very young team," Coach Steve Stratos said. "We played well in the 
first two games. We were putting pressure on the Wildcats for most of the 
match." NAIA 
</P>
<P>
 Azusa Pacific cruised to an easy, 15-9, 15-2, 15-9 victory over St. Vincent 
College in the first round of the NAIA Championships in Chattanooga, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
 Middle blocker Tiara Ainuu led the Cougar attack with 10 kills and four 
blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter Stephanie Benitez contributed six kills and 11 digs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cougars, who won the NAIA championship in 1980 and advanced to the 1991 
quarterfinals, are now 11-1 all-time in tournament play. 
</P>
<P>
 Tenth-seeded Azusa Pacific (23-7) plays second-seeded St. Francis (35-8) of 
Illinois and then Hastings College (36-8) today. 
