<P>
2 MEN INJURE OCCUPANT, ROB HUNTINGTON HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two armed men dressed in black forced their way into a Huntington Harbour home 
Wednesday night and held the residents captive, pistol-whipping one, while they 
ransacked the house, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 7:30 p.m., residents told police, two men wearing ski masks and carrying 
handguns forced their way into the house in the 4000 block of Ondine Circle, 
near Heil Avenue and Algonquin Street. 
</P>
<P>
 For about 90 minutes, the men ransacked the house and pistol-whipped at least 
one of the occupants, according to Lt. Clyde Stuart. The men then fled with an 
unknown amount of valuables and an ATM bank card. 
</P>
<P>
 After calling police, one of the residents, who have not been identified, was 
treated at the scene for chest pains by medics. 
</P>
