<TEXT>
<P>
 Taslima Nasrin, the Bangladeshi writer threatened with death by Islamic 
fundamentalists, received one of France's top human rights awards.The Human 
Rights Freedom, Equality and Brotherhood medal was presented to Nasrin by 
Foreign Minister Alain Juppe. Nasrin fled to Sweden in August after being 
charged with blasphemy in Bangladesh. Muslim groups want her executed for 
allegedly saying in a newspaper interview that the Koran, Islam's holy book, 
should be changed. 
</P>
