<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALESTINIAN KILLS ISRAELI SOLDIER IN ATTACK WITH AX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY CURTIUS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An ax-wielding Palestinian hacked to death an Israeli soldier Wednesday as she 
waited for a bus in the northern town of Afula, Israeli police reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The assailant, identified as Wahib abu Rub, 25, of the West Bank town of 
Qalqiliya, was identified by Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin as a member of Hamas, 
a militant Islamic organization that has vowed to sabotage Israel's peace 
accord with the Palestinians. 
</P>
<P>
 The ax attack came just one day after the Israeli army announced that it had 
arrested 40 members of the Iziddin al-Qassam military wing of Hamas. The army 
has arrested about 400 Hamas members in the past few months, an army spokesman 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the 40 Iziddin al-Qassam members who were arrested were several men 
suspected of helping to plan the bombing of a bus in Tel Aviv in October that 
killed more than 20 people, the spokesman said. The army said it also found 
weapons, chemicals for making bombs and skullcaps -- sometimes worn by 
Palestinians who pose as Jewish settlers to drive through roadblocks or pick up 
Israeli hitchhikers -- in the homes of some of those arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 The army said some of the suspects were planning further bombing attacks on 
Israelis in the West Bank and inside Israel's pre-1967 boundaries. The Hamas 
attacks have increased political pressure on Rabin to slow negotiations with 
the Palestine Liberation Organization on extending Palestinian self-rule 
throughout the West Bank. 
</P>
<P>
 Tuesday's announcement implied that security forces are beginning to go on the 
offensive against the organization. But Israelis had scant time to celebrate 
the news that their security forces had rounded up dozens of hard-core Hamas 
members before Wednesday's incident. 
</P>
<P>
 Abu Rub reportedly hit Liat Gabai, 19, in the forehead with an ax several 
times before she fell to the ground, the ax embedded in her head. Gabai, who 
reportedly was wearing her army uniform when she was assaulted, was rushed to a 
nearby hospital. She was pronounced dead a few hours later. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Arab ran after her with an ax," said Ilan Tzadok, a witness to the 
attack. "She stood there with the ax in her head and suddenly fell. He ran. 
There were people with guns. I stood before him. We were afraid to open fire. 
He put his arms up and walked into the police station," Tzadok told Israel 
Radio. 
</P>
<P>
 Israel Radio said Abu Rub was convicted in 1989 of membership in Hamas and 
served time in prison until 1991. But police said today that, in interrogation, 
Abu Rub maintained he is currently a member of Fatah, the mainstream PLO 
faction founded by Yasser Arafat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
