<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIX DOLL HUT SHOWS TO BENEFIT CHILDREN'S HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Linda's Doll Hut will devote six weekend nights in December to its annual 
series of benefit concerts for the Orangewood Children's Home. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 This is the sixth year the Doll Hut has staged a holiday benefit for the 
county-run home for abused children; in all, owner Linda Jemison said, this 
will be the 12th consecutive year in which she has helped organize a December 
rock benefit for Orangewood.Jemison said she hopes the six concerts at the 
little roadhouse will raise $3,000 to $5,000. She will buy toys and equipment 
with the cash and donate it to the children's home. 
</P>
<P>
 The Doll Hut also is planning a 1995 benefit album for Orangewood, to be 
recorded at the club in a series of concerts tentatively scheduled for 
February; Jemison aims to include 20 bands covering the blues, punk, rockabilly 
and alternative styles most often featured at the Doll Hut. 
</P>
<P>
 This month's schedule of benefit shows is as follows: 
</P>
<P>
 * Friday: D'Railed, Burnin' Groove, Chaze K and Heal. 
</P>
<P>
 * Saturday: Phil Alvin with Jerone Bowman, Sun Demons and Lucky Stars. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dec. 9: Cisco Poison, Mystery Train, Hellbound Hayride and Neurotones. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dec. 16: Shattered Faith, Above the Crowd, Splinter. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dec. 23: Rave-Ons plus special guests. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dec. 30: Pirates of Venus, Brat Prince, Haymaker. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $6. Linda's Doll Hut is at 107 S. Adams St., Anaheim. (714) 
533-1286. 
</P>
