</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Key Mortgage Rate Keeps Climbing: The Federal Home Loan Bank of San Francisco 
said the 11th District cost of funds, the rate to which many adjustable-rate 
home mortgages are tied, rose to 4.187% in October from 4.039% in September. It 
was the seventh straight monthly increase in the rate, reflecting the general 
rise in interest rates during 1994. The rate measures the average cost of funds 
to the thrifts and financial institutions in the bank's 11th District, which 
covers California, Arizona and Nevada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
