</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CBS, NBC Unfazed by ABC-Dream Team Venture: Executives at the two networks 
broke their silence on the 2-day-old joint venture between ABC and Jeffrey 
Katzenberg, Steven Spielberg and David Geffen to create prime-time and 
syndicated television shows. Both networks said they do not feel threatened by 
the alliance."It's a lot of nice fairy dust for Wall Street," said NBC West 
Coast President Don Ohlmeyer. "I think all it is an extension of ABC 
Productions, with the three of them as program executives." CBS Entertainment 
President Peter Tortorici said: "Anything that has the potential of equitably 
distributing risk and reward is good and wise. Whether this is a good instance 
of this happening, I don't know. I don't know enough about the deal." 
</P>
