<TEXT>
<P>
 Chrysler Voices Commitment to Build Cash Reserves: Chairman and Chief 
Executive Robert Eaton, facing a call from investor Kirk Kerkorian to reward 
stockholders, said it is "appropriate" for the No. 3 auto maker to share some 
of its growing cash reserves with shareholders. But he said the company's board 
will not change plans to stockpile $7.5 billion in cash to help it weather the 
next recession.Eaton declined to comment on what actions the board may take at 
today's regular meeting, where directors are to discuss Kerkorian's requests to 
raise the company's common-stock dividend, initiate a share buyback program, 
announce a stock split and eliminate the company's "poison pill" takeover 
defense. Chrysler's stock was $1 higher at $48.50 in late trading on the New 
York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
