<P>
 Mazda to Sell Ford-Built Car in Europe: The auto maker said it reached an 
agreement with Ford Motor Co. to sell a small car based on the Ford 
Fiesta.Mazda Motor Corp., which is 25%-owned by Ford, will buy about 25,000 of 
the cars annually and sell them through its European dealerships starting in 
the spring of 1996. After dropping a plan to set up its own production facility 
in Europe, Mazda said in October that it was in the final stages of 
negotiations to buy Ford-made cars in Europe. The vehicle will have Ford 
engineering and Mazda styling. 
