<TEXT>
<P>
 Computer Makers Form Alliance: Promising to make communicating with computers 
even easier, International Business Machines Corp., Apple Computer Inc., AT&T 
Corp. and Germany's Siemens said they will standardize the transmission of 
voice and data across computers and telephone lines.The alliance, called 
Versit, will create a worldwide standard to make it easier to send data over 
phone lines from portable computers. The Versit specifications will be set out 
this year and next in the areas of voice, video, data and networking, the 
companies said. The standards will help people using devices from different 
manufacturers exchange voice, data, images and video. The agreement includes 
products ranging from telephones to computers to personal digital assistants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
