</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 High Court Hears Arguments in Challenge to Securities Suits: The U.S. Supreme 
Court heard arguments in a high-stakes challenge to the validity of several 
hundred thousand securities fraud cases, with almost $4.6 billion in claims 
hanging on the outcome. The case, centering on the statute of limitations for 
fraud lawsuits, is a replay of an almost identical dispute that split the high 
court 4 to 4 during its last term.The controversy centers on a 1991 law that 
retroactively extended the statute of limitations on thousands of securities 
fraud cases that had already been dismissed by federal courts. The issue before 
the justices is whether Congress, by in effect ordering the courts to 
reconsider earlier decisions to dismiss the cases, violated the constitutional 
separation of powers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
