<TEXT>
<P>
 Ex-Kidder Trader Censured: The New York Stock Exchange said it took the action 
against government bond trader Joseph Jett and barred him from exchange 
membership.The NYSE said a hearing panel voted unanimously to bar Jett until he 
complies with a request to testify in connection with an investigation of 
Kidder Peabody activities. A Kidder internal investigation found in August that 
Jett knowingly manipulated Kidder systems to generate $350 million in false 
profits for its government bond trading desk. The NYSE said Jett was charged in 
April with failing to testify in connection with the exchange probe. 
</P>
