<TEXT>
<P>
 FTC Challenges Tobacco Acquisition: The Federal Trade Commission followed 
through on its promise to challenge the proposed $1-billion purchase of 
American Brands Co.'s American Tobacco Co. by BAT Industries of London. The 
commission voted 3 to 0 to file an administrative complaint that alleges the 
buyout would reduce competition in the U.S. cigarette industry in violation of 
federal antitrust laws. That triggers a hearing before an administrative law 
judge on the antitrust implications of the merger. 
</P>
