<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Report Confirms Japan's High Prices: Japan's government confirmed what many 
business people already know: Doing business there is more expensive than in 
other nations. In a report, the trade ministry said prices of industrial 
services such as transportation, telecommunications and office rentals, for 
example, were 63% higher in Japan on average than in the United States and 72% 
higher than in Germany.The report says the price of raw materials for 
manufacturing in Japan was 41% more expensive than in South Korea, 14% higher 
than in the United States and 3% higher than in Germany. Office rent in Japan 
was 1.36 times higher than in the United States; 18.80 times higher than in 
South Korea, 4.67 times higher than in Germany, 6.36 times higher than in 
Singapore, 1.97 times more than in China and 1.3 times higher than in Hong 
Kong. 
</P>
