<P>
 MEXICAN STOCKS 
</P>
<P>
 * The market fell slightly Wednesday ahead of today's inauguration of 
President-elect Ernesto Zedillo, as some investors registered disappointment 
with Zedillo's Cabinet appointments. The Bolsa index fell 4.82 points to 
2,591.34. 
</P>
<P>
 * Traders said the market would have slumped more sharply if not for the fact 
that the state development bank Nafinsa stepped in to buy. On government 
orders, Nafinsa was apparently trying to offset selling triggered by Zedillo's 
failure to include popular Finance Minister Pedro Aspe Armella in the new 
Cabinet. The Bolsa dropped as low as 2,570 early in the session. 
