<TEXT>
<P>
 French Unemployment Rate Declines to 12.6%: The nation's jobless rate fell in 
October by 17,700 people, the largest monthly decline in six years, for a 
seasonally adjusted annual rate of 12.6%, the Labor Ministry said. The surprise 
drop, from 12.7% in September, still leaves France atop the jobless rate of the 
Group of Seven industrialized countries, ahead of Italy, whose unemployment 
rate is 11.9%. But the decline, coming after two consecutive months of rises, 
was a plus for the conservative government of Prime Minister Edouard Balladur, 
which is anxious to show its job-creation policies are delivering the goods 
ahead of May's presidential elections. 
</P>
