</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEEING THE WILDERNESS ON HORSEBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF MEYERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 You can see what man has made from an automobile, but the only way to see what 
God has made is from the back of a horse.  
</P>
<P>
 -- Charles M. Russell 
</P>
<P>
 That quote by the late Western artist appears in the brochure for Los Padres 
Wilderness Outfitters, and neatly sums up Tony Alvis' attitude about the great 
outdoors. 
</P>
<P>
 Alvis, who is Los Padres Wilderness Outfitters, guides adventurous green horns 
into Ventura County backcountry. In fact, he's the county's only local packer 
making horseback trips into Los Padres National Forest. 
</P>
<P>
 The La Conchita-based Alvis supplies provisions and horses. Day trips, 
including barbecued lunch, cost $125 per person. A three-day camping trip with 
meals is $325. 
</P>
<P>
 Alvis has taken as many as 20 riders on a trip, but he prefers smaller groups. 
Riding experience is preferred but not required. Riders over 200 pounds may not 
be approved by Alvis. 
</P>
<P>
 Pack trips will begin again in the spring. Information: 648-2113. JEFF MEYERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
