<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIDBITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEO SMITH, Leo Smith is a regular contributor to Ventura County Life. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 'Tis the season for sales, something that seems never to go unnoticed by the 
folks at Mandell's Liquor & Wine Shop in Ventura. As has been the case for many 
a holiday season, the shop's extensive wine selection has been discounted 
through Jan. 2. 
</P>
<P>
 Amy Capper, general manger of the shop, said the sale tends to attract the 
wine connoisseurs in the area. "Our regulars just come in looking for 
high-quality, high-priced wines that are 20% off," she said. "We have people 
coming in spending hundreds of dollars. Sometimes people buy $1,500 or $1,600 
worth of wine." 
</P>
<P>
 As for the average customer, Capper said: "They come in, find out there's a 
sale, and say, 'Hey, I'll get some more.' " Mandell's is at 3915 Telegraph 
Road. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Peruvian cuisine has arrived in Ojai, courtesy of the month-old Papagallo's 
restaurant, a sibling of the well-respected Santa Barbara establishment of the 
same name. The Ojai restaurant is adjacent to the Ojai Playhouse on Ojai 
Avenue, in the spot formerly occupied by the Cabo Grill, and MK's before that. 
</P>
<P>
 Husband-and-wife owners Laura and Jorge Ricci are featuring the same menu as 
at the Santa Barbara establishment. "A lot of typical dishes from Peru," Laura 
said. "Paellas, tamales, vegetarian dishes upon request. Everything is made 
from scratch." 
</P>
<P>
 The restaurant is open 5 to 10 p.m. seven days a week, with music and dancing 
on the weekends. "We'll have South American, Brazilian and salsa" music, Laura 
said, "and maybe some ballroom dancing." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 If you're looking to do-it-yourself this holiday season, the Lov At First Bite 
chocolate shop in Simi Valley is holding a free candy-making class Tuesday at 
6:30 p.m. Students will learn chocolate molding and other candy basics. Class 
size is limited, so call 584-9108 to save a spot. The shop is at 5716 E. Los 
Angeles Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Tip: If you do it yourself, you get to lick the bowl. 
</P>
