</P>
<P>
 Chaminade 71, Calabasas 56 -- Chaminade trailed, 48-45, entering the fourth 
quarter, then went on a 26-8 run in Coach Jeff Young's debut at Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
 Carmine Rossi scored 19 points, Michael Yang had 15 points and Matt Jewett 
added 11 for the Eagles. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 56, El Camino Real 49 -- Moorpark's Mike McKenzie scored six of his 
22 points in the fourth quarter to stave off the challenge in the Simi Valley 
Tournament consolation game. Jones led El Camino Real (0-2) with 14 points. 
Moorpark is 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Royal 64, Alemany 62 -- Scott Hambly scored 27 points to lead the Highlanders 
in a quarterfinal game of the Simi Valley tournament at Royal. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist 85, Santa Clarita Christian 12 -- Every player scored for the 
Knights (1-0), who got 22 points from Edwin Lewis and 21 from Kevin Aust. Fred 
Madigan had seven points for Santa Clarita (0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe 58, Burroughs 49 -- Marrean Robottom had eight points, 13 rebounds and 
five blocks for the Vikings (1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Eagle Rock 71, Hoover 63 -- Ron Chambers scored 15 points to lead the Eagles 
(1-0) in a first-round game of the Burbank-Hoover Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 94, St. Francis 67 -- Brock Jacobsen had 33 points, Nathan 
Sinning 25 and Blake Jacobson 18 for the Falcons. Each of them had 12 rebounds. 
Crescenta Valley is 1-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank 62, Marshall 50 -- David Hunt had 16 points and 10 rebounds and Matt 
Baker 14 points for the Bulldogs. Johnny Diep has 24 points for Marshall. 
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 84, Glendale 45 -- Tawnee Cooper scored 22 points and added 11 
rebounds in a round robin game of the Crescenta Valley Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 69, Warren 36 -- Six players scored eight or more points for the 
Panthers (1-0) in a first-round game in the St. Anthony's Tournament in Long 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Taft 60, Fairfax 36 -- Taft trailed, 17-9, in the second quarter before going 
on a 15-0 run to take control of a first round game in the Eagle Rock 
Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe 58, San Fernando 28 -- Shirley Sotero-Higa scored 13 points and her 
sister, Lindsay, added 11 to lead the Vikings in the first round of the Eagle 
Rock Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Hamilton 49, Poly 46 -- Dora Lopez scored 12 points and Alida Gray added 10 in 
a losing effort for Poly in the first round of the Eagle Rock tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Nordhoff 41, Hueneme 37 -- The visiting Rangers (2-0) overcame a five-point 
deficit in the third quarter to win the nonleague game. Erin Barker led 
Nordhoff with 14 points. 
