<HEADLINE>
<P>
BATTLE FOR NFC CENTRAL FEATURES SURGING BEARS, SLUMPING VIKINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The surging Chicago Bears visit the slumping Minnesota Vikings tonight in a 
fight for the NFC Central lead. 
</P>
<P>
 It has been a remarkable season for quarterback Steve Walsh and Chicago (8-4), 
the surprising Central Division leader. 
</P>
<P>
 Dismissed by many after losing to the Vikings, 42-14, in the third game with 
Erik Kramer at quarterback, the Bears have won seven of nine since then and 
four in a row. Walsh has been the starter in each victory. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings (7-5) will need a better performance from Warren Moon to rescue 
their playoff hopes. The 38-year-old quarterback carried the Vikings for two 
months, but has sagged during a three-game losing streak. He was intercepted 
four times by the Jets and was sacked five times in Sunday's overtime loss to 
Tampa Bay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
