Section player averaged 27 points last season, second in the county, and her 
14.3 rebounds ranked her third. A physical force, she should again have her way 
on most nights, but the challenge is for Edison to complement Philman instead 
of relying on her. With five starters returning, the Chargers have plenty of 
experience and leadership. Height and inside play won't be a problem, either. 
But of concern is the perimeter game--outside shooting is a question mark. The 
returning starters collectively averaged 49 points last season, but only 
Philman averaged more than 7.4. Edison's goals include reaching the section 
quarterfinals. The task of getting the Chargers there falls on White, who 
coached them to a section title in 1987, then left the program. After a 
seven-year hiatus, he is back; question is, are the glory days back with him? 
