<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEFENDING TITLIST GASTON, OLSEN WIN AT WOMEN'S STATE AMATEUR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Porter Valley Country Club members advanced to the round of 16 with 
first-round match-play victories Wednesday in the Women's State Amateur 
Championship at The Golf Club at Quail Lodge in Carmel, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
 Defending champion Andrea Gaston of Chatsworth routed Nancy Markey of San 
Francisco, 6 and 5.Gaston will face Amanda Nealy of Grant's Pass, Ore., today 
at 7:35 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Chen Olsen of Granada Hills, who during stroke play Tuesday shot 75 and 
earned co-medalist honors, defeated Arlene Yost of San Luis Obispo, 6 and 4. 
</P>
<P>
 Olsen will face Yukari Horikoshi of Santa Ana today at 7:30 a.m. If Olsen and 
Gaston win today, they will meet in the quarterfinals Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Gaston rebounded after shooting a disappointing 12-over-par 83 in qualifying. 
</P>
<P>
 "I guess in defending the title there's a little more pressure," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other area players fell in the first round. Jody Duclos of Moorpark, a 
finalist last year, was beaten by Lynne Cowan of Hollister, 4 and 2. Cheryl 
Musser of West Hills was edged by Diane Irvin of Pacific Palisades, 2 and 1. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament ends Sunday. STEVE ELLING 
</P>
