<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST; CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks High boys' team has moved to second in the latest national 
rankings by The Harrier magazine and the Lancer girls are ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 Kingwood, Tex., which defeated Thousand Oaks in the Southwestern University 
Invitational on Oct. 1, is the top-ranked boys' team. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancer girls could drop in the next poll, however, as they were upset by 
Peninsula, 82-91, in the Division I race of the State championships at Woodward 
Park in Fresno on Saturday. Track and Field  
</P>
<P>
 Victoria Herazo of Canyon Country won the National One-Hour Postal Race Walk 
championships at Santa Monica College last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Herazo, a member of the 1992 Olympic team, covered 12,752 meters -- or roughly 
7.9 miles -- in 60 minutes to set a world best for the 35-39 age group. 
</P>
<P>
 The 35-year-old walker also timed a record 46 minutes 42 seconds for the first 
10,000 meters. 
</P>
